summary:
- ZIP entry handling was changed to keep security validation first, then auto-exclude fixed unnecessary directories: .git, .github, target, build, node_modules, .idea, .vscode
- Auto-excluded entries still go through path normalization, NUL rejection, absolute-path rejection, .. rejection, depth limit, invalid entry checks, and compression-ratio checks
- Added dedicated safety caps for skipped content and skipped-content accounting, while keeping analyzed-content single-file and total extracted-size limits unchanged
- Extraction now skips unnecessary entries on disk, tracks skipped counts/directories, and keeps project-root resolution based on extracted analyzable files only
- Web response/UI now can show that analysis continued after auto-excluding unnecessary content
- index/help and ja/en i18n were updated with auto-exclusion examples and pre-exclusion recommendations while preserving the existing secret-upload warning
- Added/updated tests for normal flow, .git/target skip flow, petclinic-equivalent ZIP, path traversal, NUL, deep nesting, policy-level compression-ratio rejection, and UI/help localization
- Security confirmation:
- `.git/../../evil` is rejected
- NUL-containing entries are rejected
- auto-excluded names do not bypass compression-ratio checks at policy level
- deep fake auto-excluded paths are rejected
- `.git` skipping does not break `pom.xml`-based root resolution
- existing preview/download/token/header flows still pass in test suite
- Verification:
- `mvn -q test` passed using workspace-local Maven repo
- petclinic-equivalent case passed in tests by mixing analyzable project files with a large `.git/objects/pack/*.pack` entry and confirming analysis/extraction continues
- local startup first failed because existing `RequestAccessTokenService` requires a secret in normal mode; startup then succeeded with existing dev flag `QSCOUT_ALLOW_INSECURE_DEV_SECRET=true`
- compatibility impact:
- CLI analysis core was not changed
- Web ZIP validation/extraction behavior changed only around fixed auto-exclusion handling and response messaging
- untouched user changes:
- pre-existing untracked sample directories under `samples/` were not modified
- post-processing:
- test run completed successfully
- spring-boot local run process was started for verification and then stopped
- temporary startup logs were written under `target/`
- pending:
- no functional pending items for this phase
- next phase candidates:
- add a small dedicated UI badge/list for skipped directories/counts
- add optional structured audit logging for skipped-entry summaries

untouched:
